        "title": "Add Azure Dynamic Sessions provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add `provider: azure-dynamic-sessions` for Microsoft Azure Container Apps custom container Dynamic Sessions\n- use a Crabbox-owned HTTP runner protocol (`/health`, `/v1/files`, `/v1/exec`) instead of the Python code-interpreter API\n- add config/env/flags, provider registration, docs, and a slim Azure runner Dockerfile\n\n## Testing\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go test ./...` in `worker/cloudflare-container-runner`\n- `node --test index.test.js`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `docker build --platform linux/amd64 -f worker/azure-dynamic-sessions.Dockerfile -t crabbox-azure-runner:amd64-slim worker`\n- local runner smoke: `/health` and `/v1/exec` against the Docker image\n- live Azure smoke in `francecentral`: direct `/v1/exec`, `bin/crabbox run --provider azure-dynamic-sessions --no-sync -- echo azure-cli-ok`, and a tiny synced git checkout run\n\n## Azure Notes\n- live smoke used subscription `Azure for Students` with policy-limited regions; `francecentral` worked for ACA Dynamic Sessions\n- live pool was returned to `readySessionInstances=0` and had no active sessions after the smoke\n",
